st Africa adopted the Indian samosa to be their own. Samosas are available in restaurants and streets of East African countries like Uganda, Kenya, and Tanzania. Plantain chips Everybody loves chips and plantain chips are one of them. Be it sweet or unripe plantain this crunchy snack is often found eaten by most Africans. It is often suitable for long trips and the perfect snack meal. Chapatis is another flaky snack that is handy for the go. This tasty snack is eaten everywhere in Eastern Africa and is best suited with a cup of tea. Chipsi mayai Chipsi mayai is a special snack that the people of Tanzania eat. It is a readily available meal found at the street corners and is made from potatoes and eggs while being served with ketchup. This combination can then be mixed with onions, pepper, and other ingredients.  